template {
  name: "Alchemist\'s Fire"
  category: "alchemical"
  reference {
    name: "WTC 17524"
    pages {
      low: 128
      high: 128
    }
  }
  world: "Generic"
  description: "Alchemist\'s fire is sticky, adhesive substance that ignites when exposed to\n  air. You can throw a flask of alchemist\'s fire as a splash weapon (see Throw\n  Splash Weapon, page 158 in the \\Product[WTC 17524]{Player\'s Handbook}). Treat\n  this attack as a ranged touch attack with a range increment of 10 feet.  A\n  direct hit deals 1d6 points of fire damage. Every creature within 5 feet of\n  the point where the flask hits takes 1 point of fire damage from the\n  splash. On the round following a direct hit, the target takes an additional\n  1d6 points of damage. If desired, the target can use a full-round action to\n  attempt to extinguish the flames before taking this additional\n  damage. Extinguishing the flames requires a DC 15 Reflex save. Rolling on the\n  ground provides the target a +2 bonus on the save. Leaping into a lake or\n  magically extinguishing the flames automatically smothers the fire."
}
